
[1]directly

   DIRECTLY, adv.

   1. In a straight lin or course; rectilineally; not in a winding course.
   Aim directly to the object. Gravity tends directly to the center of the
   earth.

   2. Immediately; soon; without delay; as, he will be with us directly.

   3. Openly; expressly, without circumlocution or ambiguity, or without a
   train or inferences.

   No man hath been so impious, as directly to condemn prayer.
